Juventus’s squad to face Napoli in today’s Serie A fixture has been confirmed. Juventus manager, Andrea Pirlo, released a 22-man squad to face Gennaro Gattuso’s side at the Stadio San Paolo. Pirlo announced the squad in a post via Juventus’s official website. Juventus head to the game after eliminating Inter Milan from the Coppa Italia semi-final second leg tie on Tuesday. The Bianconeri are currently in the 3rd position on the Serie A table with 42 points from 20 games. Juventus’s squad against Napoli: Szczesny, Pinsoglio, Buffon, Chiellini, De Ligt, Alex Sandro, Danilo, Cuadrado, Bonucci, Demiral, Di Pardo, Frabotta, Mckennie, Chiesa, Rabiot, Bentancur, Bernardeschi, Fagioli, Kulusevski, Peeters, Cristiano Ronaldo and Alvaro Morata The kick-off time for the match is 6 pm.